title: [Internal Compiler Error] occurred when compiling eww with latest nightly build (2022-01-21)

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

labels.name: ICEBreaker-Cleanup-Crew
labels.description: Helping to "clean up" bugs with minimal examples and bisections

body:
Builds fails only with the latest (yesterday released) `rustc 1.60.0-nightly (17d29dcdc 2022-01-21) running on x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu` compiler. Tested with 2022-01-20 compiler and it works all okay! ### Code For now: refer to [elkowar/eww:crates/eww/src/script_var_handler.rs#L137](https://github.com/elkowar/eww/blob/master/crates/eww/src/script_var_handler.rs#L137). I'll update if I'm able to minimize where actually the rustc panics. ```Rust ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.60.0-nightly (17d29dcdc 2022-01-21) binary: rustc commit-hash: 17d29dcdce9b9e838635eb0adefd9b8b1588410b commit-date: 2022-01-21 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.60.0-nightly LLVM version: 13.0.0 ``` ### Error output ```bash  eww on  master [✘] via  via 🦀 v1.60.0-nightly >>> cargo build --release ... Compiling gdk-pixbuf v0.14.0 Compiling gdk v0.14.3 warning: the feature `format_args_capture` has been stable since 1.58.0 and no longer requires an attribute to enable --> crates/simplexpr/src/lib.rs:2:12 | 2 | #![feature(format_args_capture)] | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ | = note: `#[warn(stable_features)]` on by default Compiling gdkx11 v0.14.0 warning: `simplexpr` (lib) generated 1 warning Building [=======================> ] 364/366: gtk Bu Compiling eww v0.2.0 (/home/animesh/Projects/RustProjects/eww/crates/eww) thread 'rustc' panicked at 'Expression ID not found', compiler/rustc_typeck/src/check/generator_interior/drop_ranges/cfg_build.rs:468:52 note: run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` environment variable to display a backtrace error: internal compiler error: unexpected panic note: the compiler unexpectedly panicked. this is a bug. note: we would appreciate a bug report: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/new?labels=C-bug%2C+I-ICE%2C+T-compiler&template=ice.md note: rustc 1.60.0-nightly (17d29dcdc 2022-01-21) running on x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu note: compiler flags: -C opt-level=3 -C embed-bitcode=no --crate-type bin note: some of the compiler flags provided by cargo are hidden query stack during panic: #0 [typeck] type-checking `script_var_handler::::start` #1 [mir_built] building MIR for `script_var_handler::::start` end of query stack error: could not compile `eww` ```
